    <item>
      <title>Cell-surface signals</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/projects/cell-surface-signals/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 07 Dec 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/projects/cell-surface-signals/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Uncovering the mechanisms of extranuclear auxin perception and signaling at the plasma membrane.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My research challenges the traditional view that auxin signaling occurs primarily in the nucleus. We identified &lt;strong&gt;ABL1 and ABL2&lt;/strong&gt; (ABP1-like proteins) as new auxin-binding proteins that physically interact with &lt;strong&gt;Transmembrane Kinases (TMKs)&lt;/strong&gt; at the cell surface. This work demonstrates that ABLs and TMKs act as co-receptors to perceive extracellular auxin, triggering rapid cellular responses independent of transcriptional changes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="http://localhost:1313/projects/cell-surface-signals/featured.jpg" />
    </item>
    
